# Player Controller Rules

## Requirements
- Player must extend `CharacterBody3D`
- Use `_physics_process()` for movement, never `_process()`
- Mouse look sensitivity as a constant, not magic number
- All input actions must reference named actions from project.godot `[input]` section
- Camera pitch clamped to ±88 degrees
- Sprint multiplier as constant, not inline
- Gravity via `get_gravity()`, never hardcoded
- `move_and_slide()` called exactly once per physics frame
- Scene transitions via `get_tree().change_scene_to_file()` with constant paths
